President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of Nasiru Baballe Ila as the Senior Special Assistant to the President on National Assembly Matters (House of Representatives). Ila, a product of Victory College, Alexandria and West London College, United Kingdom, was a successful businessman with interests in haulage, ginnery and tannery before his foray into politics. In 2011 and 2015, he was voted into the lower chamber of the National Assembly as a member representing Tarauni Federal Constituency in Kano. The Chartered member of the Association of National Accountants of Nigeria, replaces Umar Ibrahim El-Yakub who has been appointed Minister by the President.